'''''Vishwaroopam''''' ({{lit|The great form}}) is a 1980 [[Tamil language]] Indian feature film directed by [[A. C. Tirulokchandar]] for [[Ghattamaneni Krishna|Krishna]]'s [[Padmalaya Studios|Padmalaya Pictures]]. The film stars [[Shivaji Ganesan]], [[Sridevi]] and [[Sujatha (actress)|Sujatha]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vishwaroopam LP Vinyl Records|url=http://musicalaya.net/imgviewer.php?mod=lpcovers/1241/3/1/1|publisher=musicalaya|accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref> The film was a remake of the Hindi film ''[[Adalat (1976 film)|Adalat]]''.<ref name="Sunday" />

== Cast ==

*[[Sivaji Ganesan]] as Sathyamoorthy / Raja (Dual role)
*[[Sujatha (actress)|Sujatha]] as Savithri (Sathyamoorthy's Wife)
*[[Sridevi]] as Geetha (Raja's Lover)
*[[Major Sundarrajan]] as Rajan (Police Officer)
*[[V. S. Raghavan]]
*[[R. S. Manohar]] as Ashok
*[[S. V. Ramadoss]]
*[[Thengai Srinivasan]]
*[[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]]

